cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

The paper discusses machine learning models and their vulnerability to attacks that can infer and reconstruct the data set used to update the model. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The attacks proposed in the paper involve image reconstruction, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another possible sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques also points towards artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with data generation and manipulation, which could fall under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
